<subSubSection id="C340709AFFADFFCA7EFCFB20F69EDCC3" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="8BE52311FFADFFCA7EFCFB20F4FEDDE3" blockId="20.[151,1437,1186,1474]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
<typeStatus id="54E19DB3FFADFFCA7EFCFB20F5DADDBD" box="[151,209,1186,1212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Type</typeStatus>
material (
<collectionCode id="ED4BBBD4FFADFFCA7F22FB20F4A2DDBD" box="[329,425,1186,1212]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/pyng-6456" name="Museo Argentino de Ciencias Naturales Bernardino Rivadavia" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">MACN</collectionCode>
): 
<typeStatus id="54E19DB3FFADFFCA7FD7FB20F720DDBD" box="[444,555,1186,1212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">lectotype</typeStatus>
, 
<typeStatus id="54E19DB3FFADFFCA7C5DFB20F7DFDDBD" box="[566,724,1186,1212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">paralectotype</typeStatus>
and 
<specimenCount id="9D5CE898FFADFFCA7D65FB20F6BBDDBD" box="[782,944,1186,1212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" type="generic">
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7D65FB20F620DDBD" box="[782,811,1186,1212]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="17.0">17</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
, all male imagos from 
<collectingCountry id="F34D6381FFADFFCA7AD4FB20F033DDBD" box="[1215,1336,1186,1212]" name="Argentina" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">Argentina</collectingCountry>
: Buenos Aires, 
<date id="FFE405D1FFADFFCA7E8EFB4AF45FDDE3" box="[229,340,1224,1250]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1916-12">
XII- 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7F72FB4AF45FDDE3" box="[281,340,1224,1250]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1916.0">1916</number>
</date>
, A. Zotta col.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE52311FFADFFCA7EADFB6FF69EDCC3" blockId="20.[151,1437,1186,1474]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Discussion and diagnosis. this species known only from males was redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB5EE0FFADFFCA7AF0FB6FF075DC06" author="Dominguez" box="[1179,1406,1261,1287]" pageId="20" pageNumber="34" refString="Dominguez, E. (1987) Dos nuevas combinaciones de Polymitarcyidae (Ephemeroptera), descriptas por L. Navas. Physis, B 45, 9 - 12." type="journal article" year="1987">
Domínguez (
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7B5EFB6FF07EDC06" box="[1333,1397,1261,1287]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1987.0">1987</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. It constitutes the most Southern record of the genus. Illustrations of furcasternal protuberances (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFADFFCA7B6CFA90F06BDC2D" box="[1287,1376,1298,1324]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7B2AFA90F06BDC2D" box="[1345,1376,1298,1324]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="25.0">25</number>
</figureCitation>
) and genitalia (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFADFFCA7F67FABAF4CEDC53" box="[268,453,1336,1362]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 24, 26– 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7FC3FABAF4CEDC53" box="[424,453,1336,1362]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="30.0">30</number>
</figureCitation>
) are given. Male imagos can be separated from all other species of the genus by: 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7BE8FABAF09BDC53" box="[1411,1424,1336,1362]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.0">1</number>
) fore wing length 12.0– 
<quantity id="4CA28EF4FFADFFCA7FC0FADFF713DC76" box="[427,536,1373,1399]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" unit="mm" value="12.5">12.5 mm</quantity>
; 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7C4EFADFF73EDC76" box="[549,565,1373,1399]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="2.0">2</number>
) parastyli at least 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7D78FADFF633DC76" box="[787,824,1373,1399]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="1.5">1.5</number>
times length of its base, slightly becoming thinner towards the apex (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFADFFCA7F14FA00F711DC9D" box="[383,538,1410,1436]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7FACFA00F711DC9D" box="[455,538,1410,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="29.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="28.0">28–30</number>
</figureCitation>
); and 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7C0CFA00F77CDC9D" box="[615,631,1410,1436]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="3.0">3</number>
) fused basal portion of penes relatively thin, distal portions not expanded (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFADFFCA7F7CFA2AF464DCC3" box="[279,367,1448,1474]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Fig. 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7F25FA2AF464DCC3" box="[334,367,1448,1474]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
), becoming thinner toward apex (
<figureCitation id="13613F94FFADFFCA7C93FA2AF682DCC3" box="[760,905,1448,1474]" captionStart="FIGURES 24 – 30" captionStartId="14.[151,270,1092,1116]" captionTargetBox="[243,1335,197,1049]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[232,1355,179,1069]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 24 – 30. Tortopus zottai, male paratype. 24, genitalia, v. v. (f 1 and f 2 = forceps segment 1 and 2, k = knob, mf = median furrow, pe = penes, sIX = ninth abdominal sternum); 25, mesofurcasternal plates (fsi = furcasternal impression, fsp = furcasternal plates); 26 – 27, details of apex of penes; 28, detail of pedestal and base of forceps, v. v.; 29, pedestal; 30, pedestal and forceps (pd = pedestal, ps = parastilus)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/195436/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="21">
Figs. 
<number id="3D923136FFADFFCA7D50FA2AF682DCC3" box="[827,905,1448,1474]" pageId="20" pageNumber="21" value="26.5" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="26.0">26–27</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
